    <p>A burst pipe is one of the most stressful plumbing emergencies a homeowner can face. Water damage can occur rapidly, potentially costing thousands of rands in repairs. Knowing what to do in those crucial first few minutes can make all the difference.</p>

    <h2>Immediate Steps to Take</h2>
    <p>If you discover a burst pipe, follow these steps immediately:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Shut off the main water supply:</strong> Locate your main water meter (usually near the street or in your yard) and turn the valve clockwise to stop water flow. This is the most important step.</li>
        <li><strong>Open all taps:</strong> Turn on all cold water taps in your home to drain remaining water from the pipes and relieve pressure.</li>
        <li><strong>Identify the location:</strong> Try to determine where the burst is occurring. Listen for hissing sounds or look for water damage.</li>
        <li><strong>Dry the area:</strong> If possible and safe, use towels to dry the affected area to prevent further water damage.</li>
        <li><strong>Document for insurance:</strong> Take photos of the damage before water dries or spreads.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>When to Call an Emergency Plumber</h2>
    <p>You should call a professional plumber immediately in these situations:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>The burst is in the main water line from the street</li>
        <li>The burst is inside your walls or floors</li>
        <li>You're unable to locate the main shut-off valve</li>
        <li>Water continues to spray even after shutting off the main</li>
        <li>The burst is in an inaccessible location</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Matria is available 24/7 for burst pipe emergencies.</strong> Call us at +27 73 761 6835 and our team will respond quickly to minimize damage and get your system back online.</p>

    <h2>Temporary Fixes While You Wait</h2>
    <p>While waiting for professional help, you can try these temporary solutions:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Rubber patch:</strong> Use a rubber pipe repair kit to temporarily seal small leaks</li>
        <li><strong>Pipe clamp:</strong> A slip coupling or pipe clamp can reduce water flow</li>
        <li><strong>Epoxy putty:</strong> Can temporarily seal small holes (not recommended for high-pressure areas)</li>
    </ul>

    <p>These are only temporary measures. Professional repair will be necessary for a lasting solution.</p>

    <h2>Preventing Future Burst Pipes</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Insulate pipes in unheated areas (like attics or crawl spaces)</li>
        <li>Have old pipes replaced before they fail</li>
        <li>Maintain consistent water pressure</li>
        <li>Regular pipe inspections by a professional</li>
        <li>Install water leak detection systems</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Don't let a burst pipe ruin your home. Contact Matria for emergency plumbing service in Pretoria and Johannesburg.</p>
